Implement two advanced TypeScript utility types that recursively transform object structures:

**DeepReadonly:** Makes all properties and nested properties readonly at any depth.
**DeepPartial:** Makes all properties and nested properties optional at any depth.

Requirements:
- Handle nested objects recursively
- Preserve array types (treat as readonly/partial container, not iterate)
- Handle primitive types (return as-is)
- Support union types

Example usage:
typescript
interface User {
  name: string;
  age: number;
  address: {
    street: string;
    city: string;
  };
}

type ReadonlyUser = DeepReadonly<User>;
// Result: all properties and nested properties are readonly

type PartialUser = DeepPartial<User>;
// Result: all properties and nested properties are optional

const user: PartialUser = { address: {} }; // Valid
const ro: ReadonlyUser = { name: 'John', age: 30, address: { street: '', city: '' } };
// ro.name = 'Jane'; // Error: cannot assign to readonly property

